leaders.name: Uzma Ramzan, MD
leaders.description: Uzma Ramzan, MD, is board certified in Sleep Medicine and specializes in diagnosing and treating sleep-related issues. She evaluates and treats a range of sleep-related disorders, including chronic insomnia, hypersomnias, parasomnias, and restless leg syndrome. Dr. Ramzan began her career in internal medicine and is a member of the American College of Physicians and the American Academy of Sleep. An active volunteer in her community, she supports Habitat for Humanity and dog rescue efforts. She also enjoys Bikram yoga, hiking and gardening in her free time.

leaders.name: Diane Acosta, ARNP
leaders.description: Diane Acosta, ARNP, is a board-certified Adult Nurse Practitioner who treats a range of sleep disorders such as sleep apnea, insomnia, restless leg syndrome, night terrors and narcolepsy. She has clinical interests in sleep disorders and sleep disturbances in women.

leaders.name: Michael Coats, MD
leaders.description: Michael Coats, M.D., sleep medicine, joined MultiCare Rockwood Clinic in April 2015. He received his undergraduate degree from the University of Nebraska in Lincoln and his medical degree from the University of Nebraska Medical Center in Omaha. Dr. Coats completed residencies in Neurology and Psychiatry as well as a fellowship in Clinical Neurophysiology at the Walter Reed Army Medical Center in Washington DC. He is certified by the American Board of Psychiatry and Neurology and is a Diplomate of the American Board of Sleep Medicine. Dr. Coats is a member of the American Academy of Neurology, the American Academy of Sleep Medicine and the American Psychiatric Association.

leaders.name: Nicole Collett, MD
leaders.designation: Critical Care Medicine, Sleep Medicine, Pulmonary Diseases
leaders.description: Dr. Collett has critical care and pulmonary expertise in flexible bronchoscopy, interventional bronchoscopy (EBUS), electromagnetic navigational bronchoscopy, cardiopulmonary exercise test, thoracentesis, chest tube placement and management, intubation, ventilator management, central line placement, reading sleep studies, pulmonary function tests, and methacholine challenge tests. In her spare time, Dr. Collett enjoys kayaking, cycling, traveling, and reading.

leaders.name: Murali Maheswaran, DO
leaders.description: Murali Maheswaran, DO, specializes in treating sleep-related disorders in adults and children. He is particularly interested in Restless Leg Syndrome, insomnia, Obstructive Sleep Apnea, and Behavioral Sleep Medicineâ€”a non-medication approach to treating sleep disorders which can be effective when used in conjunction with other treatment methods. Dr. Maheswaran is a member of the American Academy of Sleep Medicine and the American Academy of Neurology. In his free time, he enjoys playing sports, spending time with family and rooting for the Seahawks.
